API.ADK

Class Driver.CANDevice.CANMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • API.ADK.Driver.CANDevice.CANMessage
  • Enclosing class:
    Driver.CANDevice

    public class Driver.CANDevice.CANMessage
extends java.lang.Object
    Subclass CANMessage. It can only be used if the Controller object has been created. initializeCANMessage(), deinitializeCANMessage(), clearFilter(byte), addFilter(byte, int, byte), removeFilter(byte, int, byte), and setFilter(byte, boolean) can not be used if the controller is started. It could produce an error if the controller is receiving message while the message channel and filter configuration are changed.
    Author:
    hroesdiyono
    See Also:
    API_ADK.Device.MessageChannel

        public ReturnCode addFilter(byte frameFormat,
                   int messageID,
                   byte frameType)
        Add an ID to the receive filter of active filter.
        Parameters:
        frameFormat - Input: The value of frame format (ConstantList.STANDARD_FRAME, or ConstantList.EXTENDED_FRAME).
        messageID - Input: The value of message ID (0 - 0x7FF for Standard frame and 0 - 0x1FFFFFFF for Extended frame).
        frameType - Input: The value of frame type (ConstantList.DATA_FRAME, or ConstantList.REMOTE_FRAME).

        ReturnCode.SUCCESS, ReturnCode.CONTROLLER_IS_STARTED, ReturnCode.OBJECT_IS_DEINITIALIZED, ReturnCode.OBJECT_IS_NOT_INITIALIZED, ReturnCode.STRING_NOT_VALID, ReturnCode.FAIL_CONVERTING_TO_ARRAY, ReturnCode.FAIL_WRITING_TO_BLUETOOTH, ReturnCode.INVALID_MESSAGE_ID_VALUE, ReturnCode.INVALID_FRAME_FORMAT_VALUE, ReturnCode.INVALID_FRAME_TYPE_VALUE, ReturnCode.INVALID_FILTER_TYPE, ReturnCode.FAIL_SEARCHING_STRING, ReturnCode.INVALID_RESPONSE, ReturnCode.FAIL_ADDING_ID_TO_FILTER, ReturnCode.WAITING_FOR_RESPONSE_TIMEOUT, ReturnCode.EXCEPTION_SLEEP_THREAD, or ReturnCode.NO_RESPONSE.
